rComments: This class was great. I learned a lot about the syntactic structure of Spanish and it really shows that Raquel is passionate about linguistics. The grading scheme is very generous and the projects are a great introduction to linguistic research.

Her class was my favorite class this semester. She is very caring and her lectures are really interesting! She makes very nice powerpoints and uploads optional readings to blackboard, so you don't need to buy a textbook. You do have to study the slides carefully for the exams, though, as some questions are pretty detailed.

I really enjoyed her class. She gives very clear expectations& gives plenty of time to fulfill them. There are many online quizzes  and such, these all work out in your benefit since she only takes the best grade. Very doable course load &she's very caring about her students. Slides are online, big deal if you miss class, but attendance is taken.
She's alright but her tests are tough

rComments: Overall, she is a good teacher but her tests are hard. I found that in the questions she doesn't specify what she is looking for so you have to over think them and if you don't really know, ask her for a better clarification. Lots of reading to do as well.

rComments: Best teacher I had for a spanish grammar course! She makes everything very clear and comes up with fun activities. Very helpful and easy to understand. Not a particularly easy marker, but a fair marker, and willing to work with students to make sure they do well.
